    "response": "To compute the **sample variance** of the data set:\n\n$$\n\\{-22, 22, 11, -19, 8, 7\\}\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Step 1: Find the mean (average) of the data**\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{-22 + 22 + 11 - 19 + 8 + 7}{6}\n$$\n\n$$\n\\bar{x} = \\frac{(-22 + 22) + (11 - 19) + (8 + 7)}{6} = \\frac{0 - 8 + 15}{6} = \\frac{7}{6} \\approx 1.1667\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Step 2: Compute the squared differences from the mean**\n\n$$\n(-22 - \\bar{x})^2 = (-22 - 1.1667)^2 \\approx (-23.1667)^2 \\approx 536.76\n$$\n\n$$\n(22 - \\bar{x})^2 = (22 - 1.1667)^2 \\approx (20.8333)^2 \\approx 434.08\n$$\n\n$$\n(11 - \\bar{x})^2 = (11 - 1.1667)^2 \\approx (9.8333)^2 \\approx 96.69\n$$\n\n$$\n(-19 - \\bar{x})^2 = (-19 - 1.1667)^2 \\approx (-20.1667)^2 \\approx 406.76\n$$\n\n$$\n(8 - \\bar{x})^2 = (8 - 1.1667)^2 \\approx (6.8333)^2 \\approx 46.69\n$$\n\n$$\n(7 - \\bar{x})^2 = (7 - 1.1667)^2 \\approx (5.8333)^2 \\approx 34.03\n$$\n\n---\n\n### **Step 3: Sum the squared differences**\n\n$$\n\\sum (x_i - \\bar{x})^2 \\approx 536.76 + 434.08"
